title: Mount Currie (Antarctica)
text: Mount Currie () is a <a href="mountain">mountain</a>, 1,110 m, between <a href="Mount%20Maslen">Mount Maslen</a> and <a href="Mount%20Merrick">Mount Merrick</a> in the <a href="Raggatt%20Mountains">Raggatt Mountains</a>, <a href="Enderby%20Land">Enderby Land</a>. Plotted from air photos taken from ANARE (<a href="Australian%20National%20Antarctic%20Research%20Expeditions">Australian National Antarctic Research Expeditions</a>) aircraft in 1956 and 1957. Named by <a href="Antarctic%20Names%20Committee%20of%20Australia">Antarctic Names Committee of Australia</a> (ANCA) for <a href="G.J.%20Currie">G.J. Currie</a>, radio supervisor at <a href="Mawson%20Station">Mawson Station</a> in 1960.
